quity for Elizabethan portrayals of prostitution and female martyrdom.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 0aClassical literaturexAppreciationzEngland. 0aEnglish dramay17th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish dramayEarly modern and Elizabethan, 1500-1600xHistory and criticism. 0aMythology, Classical, in literature. 0aRenaissancezEngland. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Renaissance.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn eBook Package Archive 1898-1999 (pre Pub)z97831104425260 cprintz978081223413840uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978151281681540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781512816815423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781512816815.jpg  a978-3-11-044252-6  Penn eBook Package Archive 1898-1999c1898d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK